The paper deals with algorithmic meta-theorems and explicit kernels for graph problems, which are typically studied in computer science subfields such as data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), graph theory (cs.GT), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The focus on sparse graphs and the use of minors and subgraphs also suggest a connection to these subfields.
